1 AN ACT relating to school cooperation with patriotic organizations.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 158 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section, "organization" means any organization identified in 36
6 U.S.C. sec. 20101 et seq. that consists of youth members or offers programming
7 to youth of an educational, civic, character-building, patriotic, or moral nature,
8 which does not disrupt the educational process.
9 (2) An organization may submit a request to the superintendent of a school district to
10 allow representatives of the organization to provide oral, printed, or oral and
11 printed information regarding the organization, including information regarding
12 how the organization furthers the educational interests and civic involvement of
13 students consistent with character education provided under KRS 158.005, civic
14 literacy under KRS 158.141, and moral instruction under KRS 158.200 to
15 158.260, to students of the school district on school property.
16 (3) Upon request by an organization pursuant to subsection (2) of this section, the
17 superintendent of a district shall provide an opportunity at each school at least
18 one (1) time during each school year on a specific school day and at a time as
19 approved by the superintendent or his or her designee for the representatives of
20 an organization to provide information to students on school property.
21 (4) The information provided to students under this section may include:
22 (a) Presentations in each classroom, presentations during lunchtime, or a
23 presentation during a special assembly; and
24 (b) Printed information provided to each student, produced at the
25 organization’s expense.
